<h2>Generate and Download Your Pay Stub Now</h2>
<p>This online pay stub generator works entirely in your browser. Fill in the form above -- employer name, employee name, pay period, gross earnings, filing status, and state -- and download a professional PDF pay stub in under 60 seconds. No account required, no email address, no payment.</p>

<p>The PDF includes every field that landlords, lenders, and financial institutions require: employer and employee information, pay period dates, gross pay, itemized deductions (federal income tax, Social Security, Medicare, state income tax), net pay, and year-to-date totals.</p>

<h2>How the Online Calculator Works</h2>
<p>The tax calculations use current 2024 IRS guidelines and actual state tax rates:</p>

<p><strong>Federal income tax:</strong> The 2024 federal brackets (10% / 12% / 22% / 24% / 32% / 35% / 37%) applied using the IRS percentage method. Your filing status determines the standard deduction applied before bracket rates kick in: $14,600 for single filers, $29,200 for married filing jointly, $21,900 for head of household.</p>

<p><strong>Social Security:</strong> 6.2% on wages up to the 2024 wage base of $168,600. Once year-to-date wages cross this threshold, Social Security stops being deducted.</p>

<p><strong>Medicare:</strong> 1.45% on all wages. An additional 0.9% applies above $200,000 (single) or $250,000 (married).</p>

<p><strong>State income tax:</strong> Applied at each state's actual rate. California uses a graduated schedule reaching up to 13.3%. Texas, Florida, and seven other states show $0 state tax. All 50 states supported.</p>

